{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":5,"timestamp":1772117732,"nonce":"fOWQA/Xun6t4yIHd1MdBFmHhlWU=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87uLpXkzwAAAAVhP-j-"},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772127357,"nonce":"GgtZI+A1U7klk/PGaCYCt4RDmBs=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87shOql","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/278#issuecomment-3968133797"},"message":"## Triage Report\n\n### Scope Assessment\n\n**Well-scoped?** The \"evaluates or generates\" description is ambiguous — these are two different things. Needs clarification.\n\n### The EnterPlanMode Question\n\n- **EnterPlanMode**: Built-in Claude Code planning. Explores codebase, designs approach, writes plan. General-purpose.\n- **plan-task**: Same, but also reads the principles review guide, checks ADR conflicts, evaluates consequences, includes a principles self-check.\n\nSo plan-task = \"EnterPlanMode + principles awareness.\" The skill should state this relationship explicitly — it adds a lens, not a competing system.\n\n### Principle Alignment\n\n| Principle | Status | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Only what's needed | **Concern** | If EnterPlanMode already plans, what does this add? The principles lens. Could the review guide just be referenced during EnterPlanMode instead? Counter: a skill makes the pattern repeatable and consistent. |\n| Human control and transparency | OK | Plan visible in work-plans/ and draft PR |\n| Capture decisions | OK | Plan captures approach and rationale |\n\n### Workflow Integration (tested during #272)\n\n```\nreview-issue → plan-task → implement → review-pr\n```\n\nplan-task output goes to `.agent/work-plans/PLAN_ISSUE-\u003cN\u003e.md`, committed to branch, draft PR opened.\n\n### Concerns\n\n1. **\"Evaluates or generates\" ambiguity**: Pick one. Suggest: **generates** a principles-aware plan. Evaluation of existing plans is what review-pr does for the plan commit.\n2. **Relationship to EnterPlanMode**: Should explicitly state it uses the planning pattern, adding principles awareness on top.\n3. **Missing acceptance criteria**: No mention of saving to `work-plans/` or creating draft PR — the workflow we tested in #272.\n4. **Naming**: `plan-task` is fine. If #277 becomes `review-issue`, lifecycle reads: `review-issue → plan-task → implement → review-pr`.\n\n### Recommendations\n\n- Clarify: skill **generates** a principles-aware plan\n- Add acceptance criteria: save to `.agent/work-plans/`, create draft PR\n- Document relationship to EnterPlanMode\n- Include principles self-check table in expected output format\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1772142546,"nonce":"qRZWShQYileA56vJj9yWBnVcAIc=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87uLpXkzwAAAAVh8ipp"},"status":2}]}